7) Sorry, not my very first, but first educational content piece I hope others can directly learn from. Hope y'all enjoy!

6) Finally, Wrapped NFTs sound cool as hell. And @doodles is one of the first to release it on a large scale: Space Doodles. Been riding since 1 eth floor, and we sure as hell aren't stopping before we take off. ğŸš€ğŸš€ğŸš€

This was my first long thread attempt, lmk what you think :)

5) Why do people buy multiple clothing items from a single high-end fashion brand? Because your style changes constantly. You want to signal your fashion through a variety of combinations; each fundamentally representing the same brand. 

Wrapped NFTs allow you to style

4) For CS:GO players, the range of gun skins you can mix and match. @Banks had a great post. Imagine you can see who unboxed your knife? The blockchain hypothetically counts StatTrak on all kills. Best part? Swapping your skins.

Wrapped NFTs add a layer to your digital ownership

3) For Minecraft players, the variety of skins you can swap between. With skin creation being fully open to players, you have the artistic freedom to dress up however you'd like. But now, you own Steve *and* every outfit you dress your Steve up in.

Wrapped NFTs enable that shift

2) For Fortnite players, imagine the different characters you can play with. Fortnite, as a brand, partners with other known brands, and you, as the consumer, can swap between Astro Jack, Lebron James, NFL players, or even John Wick.

Fortnite retains its brand, consumers win big

Fun analogies to explain why Space Doodles is changing the NFT game and pushing the needle forward. I know there are a lot of threads on this, but here is my investment thesis; inspired by @jpegrich and @degentraland
